{"article_id":"92g4bD3KmkP9TCD7","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama 's lead negotiator in the `` fiscal cliff '' talks said","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"the administration is `` absolutely '' willing to allow the package of deep automatic spending cuts and across-the-board tax hikes to take effect Jan. 1 ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"unless Republicans drop their opposition to higher income tax rates on the wealthy .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Treasury Secretary Timothy Geithner said in an interview with CNBC","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"that both sides are `` making a little bit of progress '' toward a deal","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"to avert the `` cliff ''","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"but remain stuck on Obama 's desired rate increase for the top U.S. income-earners .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"`` There 's no prospect for an agreement","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that does n't involve those rates going up on the top two percent of the wealthiest , ''","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Geithner said .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Most House Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"including Speaker John Boehner ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"remain opposed to any increase in tax rates .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Obama and Boehner spoke by phone this afternoon , their first conversation in exactly one week ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"an administration official said .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Their relations have grown frosty in recent days","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"as both sides have dug in on the issue of higher rates .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"In separate appearances earlier today , Obama and Boehner publicly sparred over who 's to blame for the standoff and what to do","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"if lawmakers ca n't reach a broad deficit-reduction agreement in 27 days .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Obama ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"speaking at a meeting of 100 CEOs ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"warned Republicans","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that he would not accept a so-called `` doomsday '' deal","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that extends tax cuts for middle-income earners before the end of the year but nothing more .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"Such an approach ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"which has been under consideration by top Republicans as a likely scenario ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"would set the stage for a big battle over spending cuts and top tax rates in early 2013","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"- all tied to the nation 's debt ceiling ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"which will need to be raised ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"which only Congress can do .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"`` That is a bad strategy for America ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"it 's bad strategy for businesses , ''","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"`` It 's not a game","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"I will play . ''","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Brinksmanship over the a 2011 debt ceiling increase","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"to avoid a U.S. default","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"cost the country its AAA credit rating","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"and rattled markets around the world .","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"While both sides say publicly","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that the U.S. will not default on its debt obligations ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Republicans believe","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"the issue could give them increased leverage","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"for extracting cuts to entitlement programs and other spending .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Boehner said at a morning news conference","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"that Obama has stifled the `` fiscal cliff '' negotiations","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"by imposing the precondition","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that Republicans accept income tax hikes on the top 2 percent of U.S. earners .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` We 're ready and eager to talk to the president","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"and to work with him","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"to make sure","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"that the American people are n't disadvantaged by what 's happening here in Washington , ''","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Boehner said at a morning news conference .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"`` We need a response from the White House , ''","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"`` We ca n't sit here","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"and negotiate with ourselves . ''","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Earlier this week , House Republicans presented a $ 2.2 trillion deficit reduction package ,","depth":4},{"id":58,"text":"including $ 800 billion in higher taxes through elimination of loopholes and deductions , slower annual cost-of-living increases for Social Security benefits and a higher eligibility age for Medicare .","depth":4},{"id":59,"text":"The plan contrasts sharply with the White House proposal ,","depth":4},{"id":60,"text":"which calls for $ 1.6 trillion in new tax revenue","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"-- largely from higher rates on upper-income earners --","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"modest unspecified savings from Medicare and a new burst of economic stimulus spending .","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"The president 's warning on the debt ceiling and Boehner 's call","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"to resume direct talks","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"comes 27 days before the country reaches the `` cliff ''","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"-- a barrage of deep automatic spending cuts and across-the-board tax increases","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"economists say","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"could cast the economy back into recession .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Seeking to avert a crisis ,","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"some Senate Republicans","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"- most recently Olympia Snowe of Maine and Tom Coburn of Oklahoma --","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"have expressed support","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"for raising tax rates on the nation 's top earners in an attempt","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"to break the partisan logjam .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"`` I know","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"we have to raise revenue , ''","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Coburn said on MSNBC .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"`` I do n't really care which way we do it . ''","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"Democrats pounced on his statement ,","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"it should `` provide cover ''","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"for House Republicans to follow suit .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"But none have so far shown willingness to accept increased rates ,","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"prompting Boehner to continue to hold the line .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"Despite the urgency ,","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"the House of Representatives will conclude legislative business for the week later today ,","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"releasing most lawmakers back to their districts for a long weekend .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"One person","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"who plans to stay in town , however ,","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"is Boehner .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"`` I 'll be here , ''","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"he told reporters .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"`` I 'll be available at any moment","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"to sit down with the president","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"to get serious about solving this problem . ''","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"Obama and Boehner have only spoken once in the past week ,","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"even though the Speaker attended the White House holiday reception Monday evening .","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"Obama suggested in an interview Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"that he has not met more regularly with Boehner","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"because of their unresolved disagreement on tax rates .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"Boehner opposes increasing them on any Americans .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"`` Speaker Boehner and I speak frequently , ''","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Obama said .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"the issue right now has to do with sitting in a room .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"Obama today continued to express cautious optimism","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"that a deal could be reached","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"but was adamant","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"that it will require higher tax rates on the wealthy","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"to raise $ 1.6 trillion in new revenue .","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"`` We can probably solve this in about a week .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"It 's not that tough , ''","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Obama said .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"`` But we need that conceptual breakthrough","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"that says","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"we need to do a balanced plan ;","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"that 's what 's best for the economy ;","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"that 's what the American people voted for ;","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"that 's how we 're going to get it done . ''","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Republicans argued","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"that Obama is moving the goal posts on taxes .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"Last year , he said publicly","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"that $ 1.2 trillion in new revenue could be raised","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"without raising rates ;","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"today ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"he says ,","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"the math does n't add up .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":257,"left":191,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":185,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":163,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":141,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":131,"right":140,"relation":"ela